entries.title_d: Alerts are going off all over the system. Multiple craft are leaving the planet's surface. You are assigned to capture the lead vessel and bring it back to the Inqusition so they can better determine a course of action.
entries.title: Dathomir System: Capture the Prison Break Shuttle
entries.thanks_5: You may have beat them this time but more will come. That is what we paid them for at least.
entries.thanks_4: You may have beat them this time but more will come. That is what we paid them for at least.
entries.thanks_3: You may have beat them this time but more will come. That is what we paid them for at least.
entries.thanks_2: You may have beat them this time but more will come. That is what we paid them for at least.
entries.thanks_1: You may have beat them this time but more will come. That is what we paid them for at least.
entries.taunt_5: Your ship will give off a nice glow when I blow it up.
entries.taunt_4: You will not have time to realize the error of your ways.
entries.taunt_3: You can't have them, Imperial dog. They belong to us!
entries.taunt_1: They paid well for our protection. Now is time to show them that they got a bargin.
entries.target_disabled: Transports engines have been disabled. Begin docking procedure.
entries.split_quest_alert: They are Imperial officers trying to get off the planet. Their computers indicate that others are trying to leave as well. Stand by.
entries.recovery_success: We have them now. Nice work, pilot. Stand by for further instructions.
entries.quest_recover_d: Move in close to the disabled shuttle and wait for the capture process to begin.
entries.quest_location_d: The vessel has just taken off from the surface. Intercept and capture that vessel inside the Dathomir system.
entries.quest_escort_d: Escort and protect the vessel until the Inquistion can get their hands on it.
entries.quest_disable_d: Intercept and disable the prison break ship before it can leave teh system.
entries.panic_5: I would rather die then go back...blow us up please.
entries.panic_4: I would rather die then go back...blow us up please.
entries.panic_3: I would rather die then go back...blow us up please.
entries.panic_2: I would rather die then go back...blow us up please.
entries.panic_1: I would rather die then go back...blow us up please.
entries.failed_escape: You let the shuttle get away. This is a disaster. Report back to your superior.
entries.failed_destroy: We needed that shuttle in one piece but it was better then letting it escape. Report back to your superior.
entries.complete: Vessel has been returned to Imperial hands.
entries.capture_phase_2: If you are not going to let us go. Just kill us. Anything is better then going back to that cursed planet.
entries.capture_phase_1: Just let us go. We don't want to go back.
entries.capture_complete: Capture completed. Escort vessel back to Imperial space.
entries.arrival_phase_2: Nav coordinates have been updated. We want that ship in one piece. Capture it...don't blow it up.
entries.arrival_phase_1: Scanning system for departing ship. Stand by for nav location.
entries.angry_disable: You don't understand! We can't go back there. You don't understand what it was like...please, just let me go.
entries.abort: Thats right! Let us go. Thank you, thank you.
